The paper discusses the challenges of scheduling and managing resources in a distributed and heterogeneous Grid environment, which suggests that it could belong to the Distributed, Networking, or Systems and Control sub-categories. The focus on monitoring and measuring resource utilisation also suggests a potential fit with the Data Structures and Algorithms sub-category. However, the emphasis on adaptive scheduling and resource management, as well as the mention of a self-organising Grid resource management project, suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the Distributed Computing sub-category (cs.DC). The Networking and Systems and Control sub-categories are also likely due to the focus on resource management and scheduling.
